canonical:
  title: 誕日齋疏
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 仰惟諸佛之慈悲所施者博宜薦吾王之壽考俾熾而昌敢殫有加之誠用扣無私之境伏念臣等猥將孱質端遇盛朝親試七人別承恩於白日幸逢千載皆得路於靑雲或演誥於鳳池或繩愆於烏府顧臣職旣皆過望而天恩俾也可忘適値誕辰恭陳梵采芥緣所締蓮鑑卽周伏願擁茨福之來崇永于多享保蘿圖之緜遠終然允臧
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 誕日齋疏
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 仰惟諸佛之慈悲。所施者博。宜薦吾王之壽考。俾熾而昌。敢殫有加之誠。用扣無私之境。伏念臣等。猥將孱質。端遇盛朝。親試七人。別承恩於白日。幸逢千載。皆得路於靑雲。或演誥於鳳池。或繩愆於烏府。顧臣職旣皆過望。而天恩俾也可忘。適値誕辰。恭陳梵采。芥緣所締。蓮鑑卽周。伏願擁茨福之來崇。永于多享。保蘿圖之緜遠。終然允臧。
korean:
  title: 탄일재 소
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 우러러 생각하니, 부처님의 자비는 베풀어 주심이 넓고 크기에, 우리 임금님 수명을 더욱 연장하도록 축수하려고, 정성을 다 드려서 부처님께 귀의합니다. 엎드려 생각하니, 신은 잔약한 자질로 성조(盛朝)를 만나서, 친히 시험하시는 7명 가운데 끼어서, 특별히 백일(白日)같은 은혜를 받았으며, 일천 년에도 만나기 어려운 때를 만나서 모두 청운(靑雲)의 길에 올랐습니다. 어떤 이는 봉지(鳳池)에서 고명(誥命)을 짓기도 하며, 어떤 이는 오부(烏府 사헌부)에서 잘못된 것을 바로잡는 일을 하는데, 신(臣)들의 직책은 모두 분수에 넘치는 것이오니, 임금님의 은덕을 어이 잊으리까. 마침 탄일을 맞이하여 삼가 축수하는 불공을 드리오니, 겨자씨보다도 작은 인연이나 부처님의 감응을 두루하여 주소서. 엎드려 원합니다. 자복(茨福)이 많이 모여서 영원히 누리며, 나도(蘿圖)가 면원(綿遠)하도록 보전하여서 마침내 진실하고 착하여지이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0330&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Buddhist Blessing for the King's Birthday
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I humbly contemplate the boundless compassion of all Buddhas,
    Whose blessings flow wide and generous.
    So I offer prayers to extend our King's years,
    That they flourish and endure.

    With utmost sincerity I bow before the unmoved heart of enlightenment.
    I reflect upon myself and my peers—
    Though of humble nature, we have been blessed to serve this glorious age.
    Among seven chosen by the royal examination,
    We received the luminous favor of the throne,
    And in this rare fortune, rarer than a thousand years,
    All of us have ascended the path of azure clouds.
    Some compose imperial edicts in the palace halls,
    Others correct grievances in the censorate.

    Our stations exceed what we deserve—
    How could we forget the royal grace that raised us?

    Now, on this auspicious birthday, I offer Buddhist devotions,
    Praying that even the smallest seed of karma
    May receive the Buddha's boundless response.

    I humbly wish that manifold blessings may gather,
    That the King's fortune be eternal and unending,
    And that virtue, like distant vines, may flourish without cease,
    Until all becomes true and good.
  footnotes:
    - The 'seven chosen' (七人) refers to those selected in a royal examination, likely the civil service examination under royal patronage.
    - '''Azure clouds'' (靑雲) is a traditional metaphor for successful advancement in official service.'
    - '''Fengchi'' (鳳池) refers to the imperial court or cabinet where edicts were composed.'
    - '''Wufu'' (烏府) is the Censorate, an official body responsible for remonstrance and oversight.'
    - The repeated phrase 'I humbly reflect/wish' (伏念/伏願) is characteristic of formal Buddhist prayer documents of the Korean court.
